Mimikslide - A simple slideshow plugin
Author: Kim Gunnarsson
E-mail:	hello@kimgunnarsson.com 
URL:	http://kimgunnarsson.com

A simple Ul slideshow plugin for jQuery

=== version 2 ===
*Added dynamic height support for container based on LI height.
*Added keyboardsupport
*Removed easing plugin

==== INSTALLATION ====

1. 	call mimikslide(); on your container like this:
	$('.container').mimikslide();

2. use default settings or use custom settings like this:

	$('.container').mimikslide({
		buttonleft: 	$('a.left'),
		buttonright: 	$('a.right'),
		randomize: 		false,
		slidespeed: 	500,
		autoslide: 		false,
		direction:		'right',
		pause: 			1000,
		keysupport:		true,
	});

3. see bellow for markup and settings, basiclly just give your li a width and height


==== HTML ====
	<div class="container">
	<div class="right">→</div>
	<div class="left">←</div>
		<ul>
			<li>1</li>
			<li>2</li>
			<li>3</li>
			<li>4</li>
			<li>5</li>
			<li>6</li>
			<li>7</li>
		</ul>
		
	</div>

	
==== CSS ====
	.container{
		overflow:hidden;
		width: 1000px;
	}
	
	.container ul{
		list-style: none;
	}
	.container ul li {
		float: left;
		width: 1000px;
		height: 250px; 
	}


For a Demo of this plugin in use visit http://mimik.nu

